sentences: Sunny Lax, born Levente Márton (Hungarian pronunciation: [ˈlɛvɛntɛ ˈmaːrton]; born August 6, 1986), is a Hungarian trance music and progressive house producer.

Sunny Lax debuted on the music scene with the 12" P.U.M.A. / Cassiopeia EP as his debut release on Anjunabeats in February 2006, which was widely played by highly esteemed DJs such as Paul van Dyk and Armin van Buuren.
He began to compete in various remix competitions in his native Hungary, performing well and boosting his self-esteem.
Sunny Lax's third single, "M.I.R.A.", was released on Anjunabeats on October 9, 2006.
In 2013, Sunny Lax launched his own record label "Sounds of Elysium" as a sublabel of Blue Soho Recordings, which would mainly feature progressive trance tracks.
